#compdef 1password2john aem2john androidbackup2john ansible2john apex2john applenotes2john aruba2john atmail2john authenticator2john bestcrypt2john bitshares2john cardano2john ccache2john cisco2john coinomi2john cracf2john
# Documentation: https://github.com/openwall/john (bleeding-jumbo branch)
#                — sources read directly from run/*.py and run/*.pl
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30
# John the Ripper *2john helpers, round 3. Extends the round-144 _unshadow
# and round-145 _androidfde2john multi-stems with 16 more hash extractors
# covering 1Password / AEM / Android Backup / Ansible Vault / Oracle APEX /
# Apple Notes / ArubaOS / atmail / Authenticator app / Jetico BestCrypt /
# BitShares / Cardano / Kerberos ccache / Cisco IOS / Coinomi / RACF CRACF.
# Surfaces transcribed from upstream source rather than from Debian
# dyn-redirect manpages (which 404).

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1

case $service in

  1password2john)
    # run/1password2john.py — 1+ Agile Keychain or Cloud Keychain dirs,
    # or a OnePassword.sqlite file. process_file() auto-detects.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:1Password Agile/Cloud Keychain or OnePassword.sqlite:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  aem2john)
    # run/aem2john.py — 1+ AEM hash files. Adobe Experience Manager SSPR
    # format converter. Identifies {SHA-256} / {SHA-512} tagged lines.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:AEM hash file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  androidbackup2john)
    # run/androidbackup2john.py — 1+ .ab Android Backup files.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Android Backup file:_files -g "*.ab"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  ansible2john)
    # run/ansible2john.py — 1+ Ansible Vault .yml files.
    # Source rejects anything other than AES256.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Ansible Vault file:_files -g "*.(yml|yaml)"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  apex2john)
    # run/apex2john.py — 1+ apex-hashes.txt files. Oracle APEX hash format.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Oracle APEX hash file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  applenotes2john)
    # run/applenotes2john.py — 1+ Apple Notes SQLite databases.
    # Typical location: ~/Library/Group Containers/group.com.apple.notes/NoteStore.sqlite
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Apple Notes SQLite file:_files -g "*.sqlite"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  aruba2john)
    # run/aruba2john.py — 1+ ArubaOS hash files. Outputs JtR dynamic format.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:ArubaOS hash file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  atmail2john)
    # run/atmail2john.pl — stdin-only, no args. Reads SSHA256-tagged lines,
    # writes JtR dynamic_62 format. Use via shell redirection or pipe.
    _arguments -s -S \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  authenticator2john)
    # run/authenticator2john.py — 1+ authenticator.data files.
    # Note: upstream writes "JtR doesnt have a format for cracking this yet"
    # to stderr; the converter exists for future format support.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Authenticator app data file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  bestcrypt2john)
    # run/bestcrypt2john.py — 1+ Jetico BestCrypt .jbc container files.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Jetico BestCrypt container:_files -g "*.jbc"' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  bitshares2john)
    # run/bitshares2john.py — 1+ files. Handles three input shapes:
    #   .ldb LevelDB files / SQLite databases / .bin backup files.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:BitShares wallet (SQLite / .bin / .ldb):_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  cardano2john)
    # run/cardano2john.py — 1+ Cardano legacy secret.key files. Requires cbor2.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Cardano secret key file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  ccache2john)
    # run/ccache2john.py — 1 Kerberos credential cache file.
    # Typical location: /tmp/krb5cc_<uid>. Magic byte 0x5 = standard format.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '1:Kerberos credential cache file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  cisco2john)
    # run/cisco2john.pl — 0+ Cisco IOS config files (reads stdin if none).
    # Single -h flag exits with usage.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '(- *)-h[show usage and exit]' \
      '*:Cisco IOS configuration file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  coinomi2john)
    # run/coinomi2john.py — 1+ Coinomi wallet files. scrypt + AES output.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:Coinomi wallet file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

  cracf2john)
    # run/cracf2john.py — 1+ IBM CRACF.TXT files.
    _arguments -s -S \
      '*:CRACF.TXT file:_files' \
      && ret=0
    ;;

esac

return ret
